Body mostly brown to dark brown; clavus and corium with transversal stripe somewhat darker than rest of hemelytron (Fig. 
1
); labial segment III, scutellum apically, marking on cuneus at base, markings on abdomen, fore- and hind coxa at least basally, tibia apically, tarsi entirely or partly whitish yellow; endosoma with elongate sclerite, tapering apically; endosoma with sub-rectangular sclerite at base of elongate sclerite, and with sclerotised area on left side (Fig. 
6A, B
); dorsal labiate plate with semilunar sclerotised rings, those rings small, subequal to ca. 0.12-0.14 of dorsal labiate plate width (Fig. 
7A
).

Known from numerous localities in the Australian Wet Tropics (Fig. 
15B
).
